no# ⚡ Binary & Bitwise Calculator

A simple and interactive **Binary & Bitwise Calculator** built using **Streamlit**.  
This app allows users to **convert decimal to binary**, **visualize bitwise operations**, and **learn about the binary number system**.


## 🚀 Features

✅ **Binary Number System Explanation**  
✅ **Binary Conversion Chart (0-15)**  
✅ **Decimal to Binary Conversion**  
✅ **Live Bitwise Operations (`AND`, `OR`, `XOR`, `NOT`, `<<`, `>>`)**  
✅ **Real-time Updates Based on User Input**  

---

# 📌 How to Run the App?

1️⃣ Install **Python** (if not installed)  
2️⃣ Clone this reposito
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/binary-bitwise-calculator.git
cd binary-bitwise-calculator
3️⃣ Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt
4️⃣ Run the app:

streamlit run app.py
📚 Understanding Binary & Bitwise Operators
🔢 Binary Number System
Binary numbers use only 0s and 1s.
Example: 101 (Binary) = 5 (Decimal)

✨ Bitwise Operators Explanation
Operator	Description	Example
& (AND)	Performs a bitwise AND	5 & 3 → 00000101 & 00000011 = 00000001 (1)
`	` (OR)	Performs a bitwise OR
^ (XOR)	Performs a bitwise XOR	5 ^ 3 → 00000101 ^ 00000011 = 00000110 (6)
~ (NOT)	Inverts all bits	~5 → 11111010 (2’s complement of -6)
<< (Left Shift)	Shifts bits left (×2 per shift)	5 << 2 → 00010100 (20)
>> (Right Shift)	Shifts bits right (÷2 per shift)	8 >> 2 → 00000010 (2)
🎯 Try It Out!
Change the numbers in the app to see real-time binary calculations! 🚀

💡 Made with ❤️ using Streamlit!
